        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25492",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=brunofriedmann",
                        "name": "brunofriedmann",
                        "displayName": "Bruno Friedmann",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Please get it directly ready for utf-8 string\nphp5 ( mb present or not ) php6 ready.\n\nIf I want to substr to 10 chars the \n\u00e7a aide chaque d\u00e9veloppeur \u00e0 se faire son opinion ....\n\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=brunofriedmann",
                        "name": "brunofriedmann",
                        "displayName": "Bruno Friedmann",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-10-29T04:45:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-10-29T04:45:02.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25498",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gog",
                        "name": "gog",
                        "displayName": "Goran Juric",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This filter should take two optional parameters:\n\n1.) A string to append to the truncated string, something like '&hellip;', ' more', etc. (this one should be null by default)\n2.) option to append 1.) to the strings that wasn't truncated as well\n\nMaybe combine the url view helper, so 1.) can be a link?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gog",
                        "name": "gog",
                        "displayName": "Goran Juric",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-10-29T09:57:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-10-29T09:57:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25500",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bradley.holt",
                        "name": "bradley.holt",
                        "displayName": "Bradley Holt",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree with Bruno that this should treat UTF-8 double byte characters as single characters. Goran, those two optional parameters are good ideas as well.\n\nAlso, I am now questioning the usefulness of being able to truncate based on word count. I would not be disappointed if that were not a feature of this filter.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bradley.holt",
                        "name": "bradley.holt",
                        "displayName": "Bradley Holt",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-10-29T10:08:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-10-29T10:08:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25507",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gog",
                        "name": "gog",
                        "displayName": "Goran Juric",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Agree about the wordcount. Strings are truncated because you need to fit them in a given space. Word count in this case means nothing at all.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gog",
                        "name": "gog",
                        "displayName": "Goran Juric",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-10-29T14:46:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-10-29T14:46:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27189",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ziro",
                        "name": "ziro",
                        "displayName": "Luke Barton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think the wordcount and round to nearest word end features should be considered. If you're going to implement something, it would be nice to have those features too.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ziro",
                        "name": "ziro",
                        "displayName": "Luke Barton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-12-10T06:24:11.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-12-10T06:24:11.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28079",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "anyone have any code for this?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-11T21:48:11.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-11T21:48:11.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28088",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ralph: You can find a WordCount filter for files under Zend_Filter_File_WordCount in trunk.\nExtract the file handling and you have a WordCount filter.\n\nOf course we should then also change the file filter also to use the new WordCount Filter.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-11T23:03:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-11T23:03:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28090",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Regarding mbstring...\n\nWe clearly have to use iconv as it's installed per default in PHP. This practice is also used in most other ZF classes.\n\nWe are only allowed to use mbstr* when there is no other way. Most things can be solved by using binaryaware string functions and iconv.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-11T23:07:54.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-11T23:07:54.000+0000"
                },
                {
